            <h2>Tympanoplasty</h2>
            <p>Tympanoplasty is a surgical procedure to repair a perforated eardrum and improve hearing. It restores ear function and prevents infections. This procedure is particularly beneficial for individuals who have suffered from chronic ear infections or trauma to the eardrum. If left untreated, a perforated eardrum can lead to hearing loss and increased vulnerability to infections, making tympanoplasty a crucial treatment option for such cases. The surgery is performed using microsurgical techniques, ensuring precision and high success rates.</p>
