            <p>Thyroidectomy is the removal of all or part of the thyroid gland, treating conditions such as thyroid cancer, goiter, or hyperthyroidism. The thyroid gland plays a crucial role in regulating metabolism, and any abnormalities in its function can significantly impact overall health. Thyroidectomy is recommended when medication or other treatments fail to control thyroid disorders, ensuring long-term relief and prevention of complications.</p>
